Coloration.
In preservative, ground color of dorsal surface of head and body Drab (
19
); head with indistinct Walnut Brown (
27
) colored reticulum; a Burnt Sienna (
38
) stripe running from the posterior border of the orbit to a point above the ear opening; light Pale Buff (
1
) labial scales and postmentals strongly stippled with darker color; dorsum with irregular, faint Warm Sepia (
40
) blotches, most visible on neck and at level of posterior margin of the forelimbs, between hindlimbs and base of tail; ground color of dorsal surface of limbs like body; venter, throat and lower surface of limbs uniformly Pale Buff (
1
